<sentence id="0">Acetylation and deacetylation of histone H4 continue through metaphase with depletion of more-acetylated isoforms and altered site usage .</sentence>
<sentence id="1">Antibodies specific for acetylated isoforms of histone H4 have been used to compare acetylation of this histone in interphase and metaphase cells .</sentence>
<sentence id="2">Two rabbit antisera ( R5 and R6 ) were used , each specific for H4 molecules acetylated at one of the four <scope type="spec" id="0"> <cue type="spec" id="0">possible</cue> acetylation sites</scope> , namely Lys-5 ( R6 ) and Lys-12 ( R5 ) .</sentence>
